President Obama has announced his intention to nominate William S. Greenberg as a Judge to the United States Court of Appeals for Veterans Claims. Greenberg is currently a Partner at McCarter & English, LLP and has served in the Reserve Components of the United States Army for 27 years, reaching the rank of Brigadier General. He has also held positions such as Chairman of the Judicial and Prosecutorial Appointments Committee of the New Jersey State Bar Association and Chairman of the Reserve Forces Policy Board at the Department of Defense. Additionally, Greenberg founded the NJSBA Military Legal Assistance Program and has received awards for his public service and legal work. He holds a B.A. from Johns Hopkins University and a J.D. from Rutgers University School of Law.